p: The yields of ER and EL were 5.01% and 4.85% ( v/ w), with densities of 1.05 and 0.97 g/mL respectively. Gas chromatography-mass spectrometry (GC-MS) analysis results are summarized in Table 1. The main components of ER included methyleugenol (28.67%), safrole (19.61%), 3,5-dimethoxytoluene (12.63%), and 3-carene (6.13%), whereas methyleugenol (27.05%), safrole (15.73%), Î±-pinene (6.84%) and 3,5-dimethoxytoluene (6.37%) were the main constituents of EL. EOs from A. heterotropoides were rich in phenylpropenes (>50%) and bicyclic monoterpenes.
